How to use this Toolkit


The Harney County Digital Toolkit was created to support the overall wellbeing of students and families in the community. This toolkit is here to help you find practical, trusted resources that meet your needs.

Toolkit is organized into sections so that you can easily explore what's most relevant to you:
For Students & Youth: tools to build confidence, manage stress, strengthen friendships, and take care of yourself
For Parents & Caregivers: ideas, articles, and activities to support your child‚Äôs wellbeing

Browse by Topic:
Coping with Stress or Strong Emotions
FInding Balance w/social media and screen time
Building healthy relationships
Feeling connected and supported
Knowing where to turn when things feel overwhelming

Some information provided can be downloaded and printed so that it can be shared. The resources provided are flexible and designed for supporting wellbeing.


This is a living resource that can be updated as needed.

