Key Metrics
¬∑      Bedtime: The time you went to bed.
¬∑      Wake-Up Time: The time you woke up.
¬∑      Total Sleep Hours: The total amount of time you spent sleeping.
¬∑      Sleep Quality: Your subjective rating of how well you slept (1 = very poor, 5 = excellent).
¬∑      Dreams Remembered: Indicate if you remember any dreams upon waking.
¬∑      Energy Level: Rate your energy level upon waking (1 = very low, 5 = very high).
¬∑      Notes: Record any external factors or observations that might have influenced your sleep.
This template can help you improve your sleep hygiene, identify disturbances, and achieve consistent rest. Sweet dreams!
